
Big O Notation:
Big O Notation is used to describe the performance of the algorithm as the input size n increases.

Example:
        O(1)      -->  Constant
        O(log n)  -->  Logarithmic
        O(n)      -->  Linear


Best Case: The element is found immediately probably in first search/comparision.

Average Case: The element is found somewhere in the middle of the array.

Worst Case: The element is found at the end or not found at all.